Michael Hanline, 69, was convicted of murder for the fatal shooting of truck driver JT McGarry in 1980 . 
  On Wednesday a judge dismissed the charges against him and he was released last November . 
  On the day of his release he ate his first burger after being wrongfully imprisoned for 36 years . 
  In a video posted on April 20 he is seen at a Carl's Jr asking for a burger 'they show on TV with the bacon on it'